    <p>The system data for building the package, including hg17, hg18, hg19, hg38, mm7, mm8, mm9, and mm10, was downloaded from the UCSC genome browser using its tool Table browser (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://genome.ucsc.edu/cgi-bin/hgTables?hgsid=1097046771_lLSM8fFqrnzE9fECLP2zBMeNfPZ6">https://genome.ucsc.edu/cgi-bin/hgTables?hgsid=1097046771_lLSM8fFqrnzE9fECLP2zBMeNfPZ6</ext-link>) with the options group setting to “Mapping and Sequencing” and track setting to “Chromosome Band (Ideogram)”. The VCF example file was generated from the GEO data set GSE149444 (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE149444">https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE149444</ext-link>), and the MAF example file was generated from the human adenoid cystic carcinoma data of TCGA database, which was downloaded from <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.cbioportal.org/study/summary?id=acyc_mskcc_2013">http://www.cbioportal.org/study/summary?id=acyc_mskcc_2013</ext-link>. The VCF files for simulation was generated from the hg38 genome data, which was downloaded from the UCSC genome browser using its tool Downloads (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg38/chromosomes/">https://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg38/chromosomes/</ext-link>).</p>
  </notes>
